<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870630-0083 </DOCNO><HL> Carolco Will Acquire OrbisIn an Exchange of Shares</HL><DD> 06/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CRCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> LOS ANGELES  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Carolco Pictures Inc. said it signed a letter of intent to acquire Orbis Communications Inc. in a stock transaction valued at about $16 million.    Carolco said it would exchange 2.2 million newly issued shares for Orbis within the next 60 days. In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday, Carolco shares closed at $7.125, up .125 cents.    Carolco, an entertainment concern involved in financing, producing and leasing motion pictures, currently has a total of 28.1 million shares outstanding, without the inclusion of the newly issued shares.    Orbis is a closely held New York-based television distribution and advertising sales company founded three years ago. Carolco said Orbis has had a good growth record and will help Carolco grow in the television distribution market. </TEXT></DOC>